'''State Route 220''' is a [[state highway (US)|state highway]] in the [[U.S. state]] of [[California]], defined to run between [[California State Route 84|State Route 84]] and [[California State Route 160|State Route 160]] on [[Ryer Island]]. At the eastern end of Ryer Island, the road crosses Steamboat Slough on the J-Mack Ferry, a [[cable ferry]].

==State law==
'''Legal Definition of Route 220:''' [http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/California_Streets_and_Highways_Code%2C_Chapter_2%2C_Article_3%2C_Section_301-635#Route_220 California Streets and Highways Code, Chapter 2, Article 3, Section 520]

